{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrange\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrange"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OrangeThemeLinkComponentTokensProvider"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Define your own provider for link component tokens","    \/\/ by inheriting from existing provider","    class CustomLinkComponentTokensProvider: OrangeThemeLinkComponentTokensProvider {","","        \/\/ Then override the link component tokens you want.","","        override var sizeMinHeightMedium: SizeSemanticToken { DimensionRawTokens._600 }","","        override var colorChevronHover: MultipleColorSemanticTokens { colors.repositoryOpacityBlackHigher }","","        override var spaceColumnGapIconSmall: SpaceSemanticToken { spaces.paddingInlineSpacious }","","        \/\/ ...","    }","","    \/\/ Or define your own provider from scratch","    class CustomLinkComponentTokensProvider: LinkComponentTokens {","","        \/\/ And implement hunders of tokens.","        \/\/ You are allowed to give semantic tokens providers if you want to define values.","    }"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, you can give this "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomLinkComponentTokensProvider"},{"type":"text","text":" to your own theme implementation:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["class LocalTheme: OrangeTheme {","","    override init() {","        super.init(link: CustomLinkComponentTokensProvider())","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"or to an already existing theme for example:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["    OrangeTheme(link: CustomLinkComponentTokensProvider())"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"par